A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This project enables development of new and novel Anti-Tamper technologies and solutions toward Department of Navy technical needs and requirements through DoN
AT Technical Authority engagement in government, defense industrial base, and commercial technology endeavors. The technologies and solutions to be developed
address and mitigate exploitation and reverse engineering threats associated with sensing, weapon, combat, and Command, Control, Computers, Communications,
Cyber, Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (C5ISR) systems and platforms when they are outside of U.S. control. The technologies include secure
microelectronics and processing, sensors, software, architecture components, and enabling technologies. The technology and solutions will be assessed and tested
for technology and manufacturing maturity, as well as suitability for DoN-relevant environments and use cases. Government laboratory expertise will mature in Anti
Tamper technologies and techniques. Factors related to integration and composition of discrete technologies and solutions will be understood and, where applicable,
demonstrated to enhance their value to the overall protection scheme and effectively deter, impede, detect, and respond to credible reverse engineering and exploitation
threats.

