B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025    FY 2026      FY 2027
- Support weapon development and weapon effects phenomenology programs with test design, requirements, and execution
support ensuring operational requirements are met and validated models are integrated into weaponeering planning tools.
- Deliver enhanced Adversarial Weapons Asset Protection Toolkit capability in Vulnerability Assessment and Protection Option
tool via a critical expansion to the library of adversarial weapons, adding the highest priority weapons for U.S. Indo-Pacific
Command and U.S. European Command.
- Mature FDDE organization and functionality featuring workshops, demonstrations and Combatant Command exercise support
using agent-based modeling for system of systems analysis of WMD targets.
- Develop and transition new pilot/exploratory Unmasking Denial and Deception technological and process approaches for finding
and characterizing the toughest "Unknown/Unknown" targets that are masked by denial and deception techniques.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Mature Full Dimensional Defeat Enterprise functionality featuring studies, analysis, reporting and Combatant Command
exercise support; furthering development of agent-based modeling for system of systems analysis of WMD targets and expanding
functional agent libraries and facility templates, including larger system of facilities and cross-domain targeting.
- Develop a robust WMD-Target Immersive Mission Planning capability to leverage target models to create a 3-D immersive
virtual reality environment for iterative mission planning; enhanced incorporation of multiple intelligence products and formats into
models.
- Finalize development of baseline Mobile Missile Launcher Fragility testbed and complete initial Small-Scale test events to anchor
new analytic approach for blast and fragment insult to WMD warhead for modeling and analysis.
- Deliver modernized and integrated CWMD planning tool operational capabilities that enable interactive targeting/management
workflows, enhanced user interface/experience, seamless cross-domain data sharing, and intelligence community-standard
graphics/products.
- Implement next generation, automated technical sensing and machine learning tools to identify WMD capabilities via
electromagnetic signatures and deliver capabilities to U.S. Special Operations Command (USSOCOOM) via hardware and
analysis tools; transition final electromagnetic detection capability to USSOCOM improving their capability by 100% to detect near-
peer strategic WMD-related signatures for CWMD operations.
- Provide offensive, scalable, and flexible options for execution of overt and discreet CWMD operations to deny, delay, degrade,
disrupt, defeat, or destroy facilities, critical nodes, and other WMD capabilities in support of Combatant Commands.
- Transition Next Gen (6G/Next G) Radio Frequency threat countermeasures capability for Explosive Ordnance Disposal render
safe operations to USSOCOM and other U.S. Government entities.
- Develop and transition next generation device for alarm and trigger bypass and work in augmented reality visualization of WMD
for enhanced crisis response in NO FAIL render safe missions.
- Deliver Device Defeat Explosively Formed Projectile and shaped charge Device Defeat Tools.
