       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2026 request for Strategic Sealift includes $14,572 thousands of discretionary and $21,200 thousands of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $35,722
       thousands. The mandatory funds will be allocated to T-AKE Expeditionary Reload Equipment. Further details regarding this reconciliation request can be found in
       Section 20002 (Shipbuilding) of the Reconciliation Exhibit.

       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $4.236 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration
       in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative."

       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $2.868 million for civilian personnel to optimize the workforce in compliance with Executive Order 14210, "Implementing the
       President's Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative."

       Program adjustments include:

       Project 3161 NAVSEA Tech Authority: Decrease due to Additive Manufacturing and Learn to Action Board efforts moving to other program elements to improve
       transparency.

       Project 3376 Strategic Sealift: Increase supports design & fabrication efforts for ASRV demonstration.

       Project 3505 Maritime Prepositioning Force Next: Increase due to additional program management support for acquisition documentation development to include
       RFPs/awards for multiple industry studies contracts.

       Project 4045 Next Generation Medium Logistics Ship (NGLS): Funds added in FY 2026 to support NGLS preliminary design efforts.

       Project 5010 AS(X) Submarine Tender: Funds added in FY 2026 supports shift from Preliminary Design type efforts to finalizing design/cost trades and design
       maturity.




