Description: The CPSD effort funds the analysis of ship system technologies to reduce design, construction and
sustainment costs, tools, analyses and technologies to reduce fleet life cycle costs, reduce life-cycle failure risk
and improved refurbishment cycles. Efforts also include the development of validation tools to certify the safety
and mission capability of platform concepts and eventually ships, development and application of advanced
manufacturing capabilities including technical properties pertaining to their application in a naval environment,
develop an understanding of the changing electromagnetic environment (EME) in the naval environment, adjust
and develop practices and standards, development and application of digital engineering processes applied to
system, design and risk assessment and aggregation, methodologies and systems for efficient and cost effective
engineering analysis and risk reduction. CPSD supports technical authority needs for emerging capabilities
associated with unmanned systems and platforms, advanced weapons systems, impacts of new materials, and
increasing complexity of modern cyber-physical systems that employ software to operate hardware.

FY 2025 Plans:
CPSD funds align to CPSD technical pillars: Ship Technology Improvement, Fleet Maintenance & Life Cycle
Cost Reduction, and Digital Engineer/Electromagnetic Environment Effects.

