       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $1.776 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration
       in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative."

       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $0.811 million for civilian personnel to optimize the workforce in compliance with Executive Order 14210, "Implementing the
       President's Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative."

       Program Adjustments of $0.476 million includes an increase for new start program requirements for the Critical Avionics Reliability Program (CARP) of the Next
       Generation Radar Altimeter (NGEN RADALT).
       Decrease of $3.167 million is for other rate/miscellaneous adjustments. This results in an overall budget decrease of $2.691 million.

       Schedule:

       Tactical Communications (TACCOM):
       FY25/FY26: Updated nomenclature from "Gen5 Crypto Mod, TSV 5.x, SINCGARS 32" to "Gen5B Crypto Mod 2, SINCGARS 3.2"; Updated nomenclature from
       "Gen6 Crypto Mod, TSV 5.x, ACC 2.x, SATURN ed.5, MUOS 4.x" to "Gen6 Crypto Mod, ACC 2.x, SATURN ed. 5, MUOS 4.x"; Updated nomenclature from
       "Gen6 Crypto Mod 2" to "Gen6 Crypto Mod 2 QR" to capture enhanced capabilities and requirements.

       Ground Proximity Warning System/Terrain Awareness System (GPWS/TAWS II): Developmental flight test aircraft and resource availability necessitated changes
       for H-1 platform starting in FY25. Funding was reinvested for cost increase of aircraft usage rates (fully burdened) as well as addition of shipboard testing. FY26
       Systems Development requirements funding for V-22 platform delays were reinvested for H-1 platform Test & Evaluation Development Testing on DT2, Northrup
       Grumman (NG)/Bell Helicopter Textron (BHT) Integration Testing on FB2 and H-1 TAWS II FB2 Delivery.
       FY25: Updated H-1 TAWS II S/W Dev FB2 start from 1Q/25-3Q/25 to 4Q/25-3Q/26; Updated H-1 TAWS II DT 1 start from 1Q/25 to 3Q/25-1Q/26; Updated H-1
       TAWS II DT 2 from 4Q/25 to 4Q/26-2Q-27; Updated NG/BHT Int Testing FB2 start from 3Q/25 to 3Q/26-4Q/26; Updated H-1 TAWS II FB2 Del from 3Q/25 to
       3Q/26.
       FY26: Updated V-22 TAWS II S/W Dev FB1 start from 4Q/26-1Q/28 to 4Q/27-3Q/29; Updated V-22 TAWS II Reqt's Dev Restart start from 2Q/26-1Q/27 to
       2Q/27-1Q/28.

       Digital Interoperability (DI)/Marine Air Ground Task Force (MAGTF) Agile Networking Gateway Link (MANGL): Schedule changes result from reconfiguring the
       DI/MANGL prototype using Non-Developmental Item (NDI) radios in place of the previously planned Software Reconfigurable Payload (SRP) due to technical
       issues with NSA certification of SRP. Funding was reinvested for the completion of MV-22 integration, MV-22 logistics analysis, Ground Node Prep/Test and
       qualification testing.
       FY25: Added Design Review #3 3Q/25; Removed MV-22 Initial Fielding Approval 3Q/25; Removed CH-53K & KC-130J AAP Approval 3Q/25; Updated MV-22
