B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                          FY 2025              FY 2026    FY 2027
Title: Mission Partner Environment                                                                                                               0.000                   -      15.464
Description: Mission Partner Environment (MPE) enables secure sharing of operational information for collaboration between
and among the United States (US) and mission partners. Specifically, MPE will conduct development efforts to include data
modeling, bi-directional interfaces, integration, and testing of MPE engineering solutions in alignment with the federated mission
networking framework to combine multiple coalition information sharing capabilities, to include modifications interface with legacy
capabilities.

FY 2027 Plans:
Develop data model with new and existing MPE solutions, correlate and map data fields between Maven Smart Systems and
existing operational capabilities for an improved common operational picture, implement bi-directional interfaces, and implement
container orchestration in Joint Operational Edge Coalition Environment nodes.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Change is due to the transfer responsibilities for Mission Partner Environment (MPE) operations, sustainment, and development
activities from the United States Air Force to Department of War CIO and the Defense Information System Agency. In FY27,
the Mission Partner Environment (MPE) portfolio will provide the foundational technology and support that enables the DoW to
effectively collaborate and interoperate with mission partners across all phases of operations.
